\cf0 The progression is striking: same group, same conceptual approach, central value essentially unchanged for 
\f0\b 15 years
\f1\b0 , while the error bar has shrunk by a factor of 3.5 as the anchor and calibrator quality has improved. This stability is the strongest argument against any "the next iteration of SH0ES will reveal a missing systematic" pattern of objection \'97 there have been many iterations, and the central value hasn't moved.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 What R22 did differently from R16\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The R22 paper is the one most people mean when they say "SH0ES" without qualification. Compared to R16, the key advances:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 42 SN Ia calibrator hosts
\f1\b0  (up from 19) \'97 thanks to a major HST program covering all suitable nearby SNe Ia from the past four decades. This is the dominant statistical-precision improvement.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Three-anchor calibration
\f1\b0  \'97 Gaia EDR3 added the parallax anchor at full precision; LMC DEBs at 1% (Pietrzy\uc0\u324 ski+19) added that anchor at full precision; NGC 4258 at 1.5% (Reid+19) was also tightened.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Improved Cepheid metallicity treatment
\f1\b0  \'97 using HII region oxygen abundances per host, with the metallicity slope $Z_W$ fit globally rather than externally imposed.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	4	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Crowding tests
\f1\b0  at unprecedented detail \'97 Riess et al. ran six independent tests demonstrating that Cepheid photometry is unbiased against background contamination in the WFC3 IR images, addressing a long-standing critique from the CCHP group.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	5	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Pantheon+ SN Ia photometry
\f1\b0  \'97 the most carefully calibrated SN Ia sample ever, with ~280 supernovae in the Hubble flow.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 The end result: \'b11.04 precision, 
\f0\b 5\uc0\u963  tension with Planck
\f1\b0 , no systematic identified that could plausibly close the gap.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 SH0ES vs CCHP \'97 the methodological dispute\

\f1\b0\fs24 CCHP (Freedman+19, +21, +25) gives systematically lower H
\f2 \uc0\u8320 
\f1  values (66.6 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  69.8 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  70.4 across iterations) using TRGB calibration of the same SN Ia ladder. The disagreement at face value is ~2\uc0\u963 . Three issues drive most of it:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 TRGB tip detection methodology.
\f1\b0  CCHP uses an edge-detection kernel approach; EDD/Anand uses different smoothing and edge functions. Same data, slightly different tips, ~1 km/s/Mpc shift in H
\f2 \uc0\u8320 
\f1 .\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 LMC TRGB calibration.
\f1\b0  CCHP calibrates TRGB partly via the LMC TRGB tip; this requires careful reddening corrections to disentangle the tip from foreground extinction. There has been disagreement about the right LMC reddening corrections \'97 ~0.05 mag swings in either direction at this rung.\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 SN Ia subset selection.
\f1\b0  SH0ES and CCHP use overlapping but not identical SN Ia samples; sample-selection differences shift the result by ~0.5 km/s/Mpc.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 The H0DN paper's contribution is to handle all of this in a unified covariance framework, so you can see how much of the dispute is statistical vs methodological vs systematic. Spoiler: most of it is methodological, propagating through differently between the SH0ES and CCHP analyses, with the H0DN combined value sitting closer to SH0ES because the multi-method (Cepheid + TRGB + SBF + Mira) consistency favors the higher value when all paths are weighted by their formal uncertainties.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 SH0ES with JWST \'97 the recent crucial test\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 A live concern through 2022\'962023 was whether HST Cepheid photometry was secretly contaminated by crowding (blending with unresolved background stars in distant SN Ia hosts), and whether this contamination might artificially bias H
\f2 \uc0\u8320 
\f1  high.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Riess et al. 2024
\f1\b0  ("JWST Validates HST Distance Measurements", ApJ 977, 120) re-observed the Cepheids in 5 SN Ia hosts with JWST NIRCam, which has 4\'d7 better angular resolution than HST WFC3. Result:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Cepheid Wesenheit magnitudes from JWST agree with HST to 0.005 mag
\f1\b0  (i.e., 0.25%), with no evidence of crowding bias.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The crowding-correction tests in R22 are validated.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The Riess 2024 combined-method H
\f3 \uc0\u8320 
\f0  is 72.6 \'b1 2.0 km/s/Mpc
\f1\b0  \'97 essentially unchanged from R22, and this is the closest the literature has come to publishing an honest "Pop-Mix" measurement.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 This was a meaningful test because crowding was the most plausible single systematic that could have brought SH0ES down toward Planck. It survived.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 Where SH0ES could still go wrong\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 To be balanced \'97 there are residual concerns worth knowing about:\
